<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en-US"
      lang="en-US"
      i18n:domain="plone">

<body>

<metal:topslot metal:define-macro="topslot">
   <tal:define define="global kupu_base_override here/aq_parent/aq_parent/aq_parent/aq_parent/absolute_url;" />
   <style>textarea#content { width:95%; height: 300px; }</style>
</metal:topslot>

<metal:footer metal:define-macro="body">
<br />
<div tal:define="usingkupu python:here.contentUsesKupu('content');
        plain python:here.get_content_type('content')=='plain';">

<div tal:condition="usingkupu">This content will be filtered when
saved or displayed. To avoid filtering, use the 'Suppress
Kupu' link and select the content type 'Plain Text'.<br />

<a class="context" href="#" tal:attributes="href
string:${here/absolute_url}/base_edit?kupu.suppress=content">Suppress
Kupu</a>

</div>
<div tal:condition="not:usingkupu">Kupu is not currently being used to edit this content.
<ul>

<li> If the selected content type is 'Plain Text' you may enter raw
HTML in the edit area and it will not be filtered or changed in any
way.  </li>

<li> If the selected content type is 'HTML' Kupu will be used next
time you edit this page and the content may be modified when rendered.
</li>

<li> The 'edit with kupu' link below will convert the plain text to
HTML (i.e. tags will display). Use this only if you wish to paste some
plain text and then convert it to HTML. To start using Kupu without
converting the text simply change the content type.
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<metal:use-macro use-macro="here/edit_macros/macros/body" />
</metal:footer>

</body>
</html>
